      <p class="mt-4 text-base text-[var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        Thanks to Philip Guo and David Engler for the original IncPy. The core idea is
        theirs: watch a Python script as it runs, find the function calls that are pure
        and slow, store their results so they don't have to run again. rote rebuilds that
        on Python 3.12 and the libraries that have shipped since 2011. Any flaws in the
        reimplementation are ours.
